      "Finger placed in taped splint",
      "Work area flagged off to prevent non-essential personnel entry"
    ],
    "summary": "On 22 November 2023 at approximately 1125 hours, a construction worker with Burner Fire Control sustained a fractured right index finger when the finger was pinched between an eight-foot section of two-inch diameter airline piping and an I-beam while the piping was being lowered from an elevated pipe rack on Mobile 916 Platform AP in the Gulf of Mexico. The incident resulted in a Loss Time Accident exceeding three days, with the injured person requiring approximately four to six weeks before returning to work.",
